    "## 2.3 Leakage-Safe Aggregated Features\n",
    "\n",
    "Leakage-safe aggregation ensures that historical risk patterns are learned only from the training data and then applied to unseen test transactions.\n",
    "\n",
    "- Customer statistics capture normal spending and distance behavior without using future information\n",
    "- Merchant, category, and state fraud rates provide contextual risk signals learned from past observations\n",
    "- Age-band fraud rates add demographic context while preserving a realistic modeling setup\n",
    "\n",
    "This approach is important because it prevents information from the test set from leaking into feature construction, making model evaluation more reliable and closer to real-world deployment."
   ]
