    "---\n",
    "## 2.4 Sequential Features\n",
    "\n",
    "Sequential features capture the **order and timing of transactions**, which is critical in fraud detection.\n",
    "\n",
    "- `time_since_last_txn_sec` helps identify unusually rapid transactions, which may indicate fraud bursts or automated activity  \n",
    "- `prev_amt`, `amt_change_from_prev`, and `amt_ratio_to_prev` detect sudden spikes or drops in spending behavior  \n",
    "- Same-day features (`customer_txn_same_day`, `customer_amt_same_day`) reveal abnormal transaction intensity within a short time window  \n",
    "\n",
    "These features shift the model from viewing transactions as isolated events to understanding them as part of a **behavioral sequence**.\n",
    "\n",
    "This is powerful because fraud often occurs as **patterns over time**, not just single unusual transactions."
   ]
