    "## 3.2 What SMOTE Does\n",
    "\n",
    "SMOTE (Synthetic Minority Oversampling Technique):\n",
    "\n",
    "- Generates **synthetic fraud examples**\n",
    "- Uses **feature-space interpolation** (not duplication)\n",
    "- Creates *new realistic fraud patterns* between existing fraud points\n",
    "\n",
    "After SMOTE:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Non-fraud (0):** 1,289,169  \n",
    "- **Fraud (1):** 1,289,169  \n",
    "\n",
    "Perfectly balanced dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 3.3 Why This is Important\n",
    "\n",
    "Without SMOTE:\n",
    "- Model becomes **biased toward majority class**\n",
    "- Fraud detection recall = **very low**\n",
    "- High **false negatives** (dangerous in real-world)\n",
    "\n",
    "With SMOTE:\n",
    "- Model **learns fraud patterns better**\n",
    "- Improves:\n",
    "  - Recall (detecting fraud)\n",
    "  - F1-score\n",
    "- Enables model to **focus on minority behavior**"
   ]
