    "#### Insight \n",
    "\n",
    "XGBoost consistently outperforms Random Forest across all thresholds:\n",
    "\n",
    "- At **low thresholds (0.1–0.3)**:\n",
    "  - Much higher precision than Random Forest  \n",
    "  - Fewer false positives for the same recall  \n",
    "\n",
    "- At **mid thresholds (~0.5–0.65)**:\n",
    "  - Strong balance between precision and recall  \n",
    "  - Example at 0.6:\n",
    "    - Precision ≈ 0.78  \n",
    "    - Recall ≈ 0.95  \n",
    "    - F1-score ≈ 0.85  \n",
    "\n",
    "- At **high thresholds (>0.8)**:\n",
    "  - Maintains high precision (>0.89)\n",
    "  - Retains better recall compared to Random Forest\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Key Insight\n",
    "\n",
    "XGBoost dominates Random Forest across the entire threshold spectrum:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Higher precision at the same recall  \n",
    "- Lower false positives for equivalent fraud detection  \n",
    "- Better F1-scores at nearly all thresholds  \n",
    "\n",
    "This confirms that:\n",
    "\n",
    "> XGBoost is not just a better model — it is a more controllable and reliable system for decision-making.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Optimal Threshold Selection\n",
    "\n",
    "The choice of threshold depends on business priorities:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Fraud prevention priority (maximize recall):**\n",
    "  - Use lower threshold (~0.3–0.5)  \n",
    "  - Accept more false positives to catch nearly all fraud  \n",
    "\n",
    "- **Customer experience priority (reduce false alarms):**\n",
    "  - Use higher threshold (~0.7–0.85)  \n",
    "  - Minimize disruption to legitimate users  \n",
    "\n",
    "- **Balanced strategy (recommended):**\n",
    "  - Threshold ≈ **0.6**\n",
    "  - Provides strong recall while maintaining acceptable precision  \n",
    "  - Best trade-off for most real-world fraud systems  \n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Business Interpretation\n",
    "\n",
    "This analysis highlights a critical real-world insight:\n",
    "\n",
    "> The model itself is not the final decision-maker — the threshold is.\n",
    "\n",
    "By tuning the threshold:\n",
    "\n",
    "- The same model can behave like a **strict fraud detector**  \n",
    "- Or like a **customer-friendly filter**  \n",
    "\n",
    "This flexibility is essential in production systems where costs of errors are asymmetric.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Final Takeaway\n",
    "\n",
    "While both models perform well, **XGBoost combined with threshold tuning provides the most practical and deployable solution**.\n",
